[2] Dominican Republic
Date: Sun 20 Jun 2010
Source: El Nacional [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.elnacional.com.do/nacional/2010/6/19/51884/Alarma-brote-dengue-en-Santiago>


An outbreak of classical dengue and DHF affects children and elderly
people in the city [Santo Domingo] in a way so alarming that the
physicians are greatly worried because of the high morbidity rate in
the Public Health Centers and private [health care facilities].

The President of the Santiago branch of the Dominican Medical
Association, Dr. Antonio Jose Checo, said that the authorities are
aware of the situation. He said, as an example, that in the Union
Medical Clinic's intensive care unit, there are 10 children admitted
under care. He cited the Arturo Grullon Hospital as another of the
centers where there are many [dengue] admissions. He said that
although he does not have the statistics at hand, there are reports
of various deaths due to the disease.

Dr. Checko attributed the dengue outbreak to the lack of a good
educational campaign to orient the citizens about the necessity to
fumigate and eliminate mosquito breeding sites and the use of bleach
in containers of clean water.

--
