[3] Venezuela
Date: 22 Jun 2010
Source: El Nacional [in Spanish, tran. Corr.SB, summ. Mod.TY edited]
<http://www.ultimasnoticias.com.ve/capriles/cadena-global/detalle.aspx?idart=3156278&idcat=56750&tipo=2&Coment=S>


According to the Epidemiological Bulletin 22 issued by the Ministry
of Health, the dengue epidemic has been declared throughout the
national territory, since in all states the trend of occurrence of
cases is rising and numerous. The report states that up to 5 Jun this
year [2010], there is a cumulative [total of] 41 573 dengue cases in
the entire country. During the last 10 weeks, likely cases of dengue
in the Capital District increased from 90 reported in the 1st week to
315 reported in the 10th, an increase of 350 percent in occurrence.

Of the 41 573 reported cases of dengue, 4136 are DHF. This week
across the country, 3399 cases were reported compared with same
period last year [2009], representing an increase of over 500 percent.

The states with most cases reported during the week of 30 May-5 Jun
[2010] are: Tachira (435 [cases]), Miranda (425), Merida (423),
Capital District (315) and Zulia, (295).

[Byline: Angela Rodriguez]

