[5] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Thu 17 Jun 2010
Source: Estadao [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,mg-tem-17-mortes-e-195-mil-casos-de-dengue-em-2010,568063,0.htm>


Minas Gerais has 17 deaths and 195 640 [dengue] cases with 110 DHF
cases in 2010 according to a bulletin released by the state
Secretariat of Health. Another 61 deaths are under investigation; in
addition to these, there are another 29 deaths from dengue with
complications. Deaths from DHF have increased to 17 this year [2010]
in Minas Gerais.

The deaths occurred in the municipalities of Belo Horizonte, Juiz de
Fora, Carangola, Santa Luzia, Arcos, Frei Inocencio, Paraopeba,
Vespasiano, Dores do Indaia, Pirapetinga, Ponte Nova, Cana Verde and
Nova Lima. Just in Belo Horizonte, there were 52 254 dengue cases
registered. The cities of Betim and Contagem have 15 776 and 6181
cases, respectively.

