[8] Colombia (Huila)
Date: Thu 24 Jun 2010
Source: La Nacion.com.co [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.lanacion.com.co/2010/06/24/huila-en-epidemia-por-dengue/>


The numbers presented in the legislative assembly are worrying. In
Huila, there have been 5278 [dengue] cases, of which 3922 were
confirmed and 898 were serious cases. There are 11 registered
[dengue] deaths. In the country, there were 106 [dengue] deaths. The
department [state or province equivalent] Secretary of Health,
Eugenio Carrera, stated that the fatality rate in the department is
1.2 on average per 100 inhabitants [in the department] versus 1.5
percent nationally.

